{"article_id":"U1aFcEeJ4aOfFJnm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The website repair gives Democrats a badly needed psychological boost .","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"Obamacare troubles remain","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"For House Democratic Caucus Chairman Xavier Becerra , the new , improved Obamacare website is better","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"than it was","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"-","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"but the law won ' t be a success","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"\" until every American","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"who has a chance","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"to qualify for these health insurance policies","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"gets it . \"","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"For Jeremy Milarsky ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"who works for one of the \" navigator \" groups in Missouri","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"that ' s helping people sign up ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"the website is improved enough","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to make the job easier ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"mainly because of a new health plan browser feature","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that actually works .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"But for health insurers across the country , the new HealthCare.gov isn ' t even close to a success","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"- and won ' t be","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"until the Obama administration finishes the critical parts","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that aren ' t even built yet .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"The fixes to the federal Obamacare enrollment website are holding up well enough","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"- so far -","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"that they mark a small but crucially important milestone in the rollout of President Barack Obama ' s signature health care law .","depth":4},{"id":24,"text":"For the first time since October , Democrats are ready to go on the offensive again ,","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"and advocates of the law are ready to start inviting people back .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"And Republicans are saying ,","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"hey , it was never all about the website anyway .","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"But the administration ' s seeming success","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"in bringing the website up to a basic level of competency","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"is nowhere close to the kind of turnaround","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that would reboot the whole conversation","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"- or make anyone ready to declare the Affordable Care Act a success .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Whole sections of the \" back end \" of the website , the part","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"insurers deal with ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"remain unfinished .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"Democrats are now questioning the Obama administration about how it ' s fixing the faulty enrollment records","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"the website has been spitting out ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"to make sure","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"people don ' t find out","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"they can ' t use their new insurance after all .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"And there are so many other real and potential problems","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"- canceled policies , \" sticker shock \" and the possibility","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"that people in certain situations won ' t be able to keep their doctors -","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"that Republicans have lots of ways to change the subject","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"and keep the attacks coming .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"The website repair won ' t erase two months of lost time on the rollout .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"But it ' s a big enough deal","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"to give Democrats and other Obamacare supporters a badly needed psychological boost","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that two weeks ago seemed a longshot","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"-","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"and for many of them , that ' s good enough .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"\" I think","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"it ' s doing better ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"and that ' s significant .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"But that doesn ' t mean you can declare it a success , \"","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"said Rep. Diana DeGette","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"( D-Colo. ) .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"\" I just don ' t think","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"you can say","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"it ' s a success or a failure","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"based on one day or event .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"It ' s a moving target . \"","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"The White House has been more mixed in its definitions of success .","depth":4},{"id":64,"text":"Obama sounded bullish at times","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"when he hit the campaign trail for the law again on Tuesday .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"\" The bottom line is this law is working","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"and will work into the future , \"","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"he said ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"as he reminded his audience of popular benefits like coverage of pre-existing conditions , free preventive care and the end of lifetime limits on health benefits .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"But he was also cautious about declaring the website totally fixed .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"\" We ' ve learned not to make wild promises","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"about how perfectly smooth it ' s going to be at all times , \"","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"But he vowed","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"that \" we ' re going to keep on working","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"to fix whatever problems come up in any startup \" -","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"and he was confident enough","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"to declare to Republicans","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"that \" we ' re not going back . \"","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"One of the most immediate problems","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"the administration has to fix","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"is the parts of the website","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"that don ' t even exist yet .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"The administration still has to build three critical \" back end \" pieces","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"that insurers need .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"One is the part","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"that handles \" reconciliation , \"","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"where insurers double-check who ' s enrolled in which health plans at what prices .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"That ' s especially important ,","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"since some insurers say","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"they ' re not certain","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"they ' re getting the records of everyone","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"who has enrolled .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"The other pieces are the payment system","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that will pay the federal Obamacare subsidies to the insurers","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"- due in late January for everyone","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"who has enrolled by mid-December -","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"and the parts","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that will compensate insurers","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"that attract too many sick people .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"To health insurers ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"whose cooperation the Obama administration needs","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"to get people covered ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"the repair effort won ' t be a success","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"until all of those pieces are in place .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"\" In addition to addressing the ongoing problems with the enrollment files , other ' back end ' functions , such as reconciliation and the processing of subsidy payments , need to be working","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"to ensure","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"the new marketplace is stable","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"and consumers ' coverage is not disrupted , \"","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"said Robert Zirkelbach , a spokesman for America ' s Health Insurance Plans , the main trade group for health insurance companies .","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Julie Bataille , a spokeswoman for the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services ,","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"which is implementing the law ,","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"told reporters Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"that the administration is \" working to make sure with the fixes in place that we ' ve addressed the most significant back-end issues","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"and that we will work with [ health insurers ]","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"so that we get accurate , timely enrollment information for them and for consumers . \"","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Still , for a website","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"that had a rollout as disastrous as HealthCare.gov","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"- the federal health insurance exchange","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"that serves 36 states -","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"it was a small victory for the administration","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"that the site hasn ' t crashed since the relaunch .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"People did experience delays and \" please wait \" messages on Monday ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"when a million visitors checked out the site","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"and some got placed in a new cyber-holding queue .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"But the site didn ' t go down ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"and it ran more smoothly on Tuesday .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":255,"left":173,"right":254,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":173,"left":151,"right":172,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":148,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":129,"right":147,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":147,"left":136,"right":146,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":131,"right